\end

! Set a filed through a button
The below macro sets the `note` filed of myTiddler to `myVal`. If `myVal` is omitted, the default value (100) will be set! When myTiddler is not existed, it will be created.


```
\define setNote(myVal:"100")
<$button>Push me
<$action-setfield $tiddler="myTiddler" $field="note" $value=$myVal$/>
</$button>
\end
```
* Example

<<setNote "Hi, this is a note">>